The White House Press Secretary Robert Gibbs gave a briefing on September 10, 2009. He discussed President Obama's upcoming events at the United Nations General Assembly, including his address to the U.N. General Assembly and his attendance at the climate change summit. Gibbs also mentioned that President Obama will chair a summit-level meeting of the U.N. Security Council on nuclear non-proliferation and nuclear disarmament, and he will host a meeting with countries that contribute the largest numbers of troops and police to U.N. peacekeeping operations. The briefing also covered topics such as health care reform, Iran's nuclear program, and the release of the Pan Am 103 bomber.